snippet.textDisplay: Frozen veggies and fruit have continued to have a bad name outside Canada and the States because Clarence Birdseye invented the freezing process here, and other US companies took the idea and ran with it.  This means that peas grown here in Oregon are usually flash frozen within an hour of being harvested rather than being poured into boxes and trucked to packing houses, then to markets.  If you want fresher than frozen, grow them yourself and eat them as you snap them off the growing vine.
snippet.textOriginal: Frozen veggies and fruit have continued to have a bad name outside Canada and the States because Clarence Birdseye invented the freezing process here, and other US companies took the idea and ran with it.  This means that peas grown here in Oregon are usually flash frozen within an hour of being harvested rather than being poured into boxes and trucked to packing houses, then to markets.  If you want fresher than frozen, grow them yourself and eat them as you snap them off the growing vine.
